article.headline: Brown 76, Yale 71
article.story: NEW HAVEN, Conn. (AP) -- Mark McAndrew scored all 27 of his points in the second half as Brown rallied for a 76-71 Ivy League win at Yale on Saturday. McAndrew, a junior guard, played just four minutes in the first half because of foul trouble. However, he made nine of 11 shots in the second half, including four of five 3-pointers, while playing all 20 minutes. Damon Huffman added 16 points for Brown (6-11, 1-1). Junior guard Eric Flato led Yale (5-10, 1-1) with 23 points. The Bulldogs led by as many as 10 points in the first half and 39-33 at halftime, one week after beating Brown 56-42 in Providence, R.I. McAndrew's effort was part of a wild second half in which Brown coach Craig Robinson was ejected from the game, picking up his second technical foul with 8:06 remaining and his team leading 58-57. Yale regained the lead when Flato made both free throws from the technical, but Brown wouldn't trail after McAndrew made two free throws with 6:54 remaining. The Bulldogs tied the game at 63 with 4:32 left on Sam Kaplan's inside basket before a McAndrew 3-pointer 34 seconds later gave the Bears the lead for good.
